{"id":19646,"date":"2024-01-02T15:22:31","date_gmt":"2024-01-02T23:22:31","guid":{"rendered":"https:\/\/www.ronperrier.net\/?p=19646"},"modified":"2024-07-15T04:21:16","modified_gmt":"2024-07-15T11:21:16","slug":"ymir-mountain-via-ymir-bowl-half-dome","status":"publish","type":"post","link":"https:\/\/www.ronperrier.net\/2024\/01\/02\/ymir-mountain-via-ymir-bowl-half-dome\/","title":{"rendered":"YMIR MOUNTAIN VIA YMIR BOWL \/ HALF DOME"},"content":{"rendered":"<p><em>An off-trail traversing the boulders and scree in the Ymir Bowl. Climb Ymir Mountain.\u00a0<\/em><\/p>\n<p><strong>Difficulty:<\/strong> C2 difficult<br \/>\n<strong>Distance:<\/strong> \u00a0round trip: 6.7 km<br \/>\n<strong>Elevation:\u00a0<\/strong>+760m<br \/>\n<strong>Season:\u00a0<\/strong>mid-July to late September<\/p>\n<p><strong>Drive <\/strong>up Whitewater Ski Hill Road and park.<\/p>\n<p><strong>Trail. <\/strong>There are two main hiking routes up Ymir, both are off-trail.<br \/>\nThe west ridge. The normal way.<br \/>\nThe north ridge via Half Dome was developed in 2024.<br \/>\nConnecting these two could make a nice loop. The Half Dome route involves scrambling and may be easier going up.<\/p>\n<p><strong>WEST RIDGE<\/strong><br \/>\nWalk past the Whitewater Ski Lodge to ascend the \u2018Lower Sluice Box\u2019 run, aiming straight for Ymir Mountain on an old rough road that quickly narrows into a footpath.<br \/>\nCross a road, walk up about 10m, then the trail resumes. At a boulder field, the trail disappears.<br \/>\nFor the west ridge, cut straight across the bowl finding your route. Going left up the boulder field goes to the north ridge via Half Dome.<br \/>\nAim for a long narrow chute to the left of some steep rocky bluffs. After 1.5 hours of hiking, reach the ridge and find faint bits of trail among the rocks. It\u2019s a steady uphill climb with a few cliffy patches. Near the summit, drop down into a deep notch with a chute far below by going onto the south slope.<br \/>\nSign the summit register<br \/>\n<strong><em>Descent. <\/em><\/strong>Rather than descending the north ridge, it may be simpler to return the same way.<\/p>\n<p><strong>NORTH RIDGE VIA HALF DOME<br \/>\n<\/strong>This is a scramble. Half Dome is a prominent landmark on Ymir Peak\u2019s ridge. The trail is still in development.<\/p>\n<p><strong>Difficulty:<\/strong> Difficult C3<br \/>\n<strong>Distance one-way:<\/strong> 4.4 km<br \/>\n<strong>Elevation:<\/strong>\u00a0+680m<br \/>\n<strong>Season:<\/strong> mid-July to late September<\/p>\n<p><strong>Drive:<\/strong> Whitewater Ski Hill Road and park at Hummingbird Lodge.<\/p>\n<p><strong>Trail.<\/strong> The trailhead is in the RV campground heading up Quartz Ski Way Trail that switchbacks up the ski runs. At 0.3km, go left. Pass below the Raven Chair<br \/>\n2.1km. Continue east up the Silver King Ridge Trail. At the top of the ridge, go southeast towards Half Dome.<br \/>\n3.8km. Go over a bump on the ridge.<br \/>\n4.2 km and 100 m higher. Summit of Half Dome. Ymir Peak dominates the view southeast. The route to Ymir involves more scrambling.<br \/>\n<strong>Descend<\/strong> on Silver King Ridge Trail, past the winter lodge at Whitewater Ski Resort and cross the parking lots to your car.<br \/>\nOr traverse Ymir Peak for a big loop down the west ridge of Ymir.<\/p>\n<p><strong>References:<\/strong><br \/>\n<a href=\"https:\/\/westkootenayhiking.ca\/?s=ymir+mountain+\">https:\/\/westkootenayhiking.ca\/ymir-mountain\/\u00a0<\/a><br \/>\nhttps:\/\/www.alltrails.com\/explore\/trail\/canada\/british-columbia\/ymir-mountain-and-half-dome<\/p>\n","protected":false},"excerpt":{"rendered":"<p>An off-trail traversing the boulders and scree in the Ymir Bowl. Climb Ymir Mountain.\u00a0 Difficulty: C2 difficult Distance: \u00a0round trip: 6.7 km Elevation:\u00a0+760m Season:\u00a0mid-July to late September Drive up Whitewater Ski Hill Road and park. Trail. There are two main &hellip; <a href=\"https:\/\/www.ronperrier.net\/2024\